Solution: Improve the implementation:
- remove busy wait;
- only retry connection errors;
- simplify the code;
- make custom headers overwrite common headers, not vice versa;
- add some more tests;
- remove obsolete await_transaction;
- make the linter pass.

PR #129 added 2 params to 
```
class PDFTextDevice(PDFDevice):
  def render_string(self, textstate, seq, ncs, graphicstate)
```
but not to
```
class TagExtractor(PDFDevice)
  def render_string(self, textstate, seq):
```
(nor to the PDFDevice base class abstract method)

which caused errors when parsing files with the TagExtractor
